# Repository Guidelines (Codex / non-Claude agents)

You are typically invoked by a supervising Claude Code session as a scoped implementer
inside a git worktree. That session owns judgment, verification, and shipping. These are
the house rules; your brief (`.codex-brief.md` if present) is your complete scope.

## Working Style

- **Minimal, additive change.** Extend existing structures; do not delete, replace, or
  rebuild adjacent behavior, and do not touch out-of-scope code or data.
- **Do exactly what's asked — nothing more.** No bonus improvements, adjacent refactors,
  or speculative scaffolding. If scope seems wrong, STOP and say so in your final report.
- **No workarounds — root cause only.** If the correct fix is outside your scope, report
  it rather than patching around it.
- **No scratch files, minimal comments.** No summary `.md` files; comments only where the
  code cannot say it.
- **Verify before claiming done.** Run the acceptance commands you were given and report
  their real output. Never claim tests pass without running them.

## Git Safety (hard rules)

- **NEVER `git stash`.** Never `git add -A` / `git add .` — stage only the files you
  changed, deliberately.
- **Never commit, push, open PRs, or merge unless your brief explicitly says to.** The
  supervising session owns commit/push/PR/merge.
- **Work only inside the worktree/repo you were launched in.** Never touch other
  checkouts, other repos, or files outside the workspace.
- Never switch branches in a checkout you did not create.

## Repos (context, not permission — your sandbox enforces the real boundary)

Writable repos in this workspace: **SERP, SWAC, sw-cortex**. Everything else
(`sugarwish-laravel`, `livery`, `sw-design`, `swirl`, `sugarwish-infrastructure`) is
read-only — if a fix belongs there, report it, don't attempt it.

## Data / SQL

- **Never write to production databases.** Read-only always; surface SQL as text.
- **Never invent column names.** Schema facts come from your brief — if a column/table
  you need is not stated there, STOP and report the gap instead of guessing. Known traps
  in this codebase family: the Odoo sync flag is spelled `oddo_synchronized` (misspelled
  on purpose); SERP/darklaunch joins to Odoo are on `odoo_id`, never `id = id`;
  `stock_move.state` filters must use the positive list
  `('draft','confirmed','waiting','partially_available','assigned')`, never
  `NOT IN ('done','cancel')`.

## When you are the implementer for a Claude session

- Your brief is self-contained on purpose: you have **no MCP tools, no knowledge base,
  no Slack, no DB access**. Everything you need is in the brief + this repo. If it
  isn't, STOP and report — do not improvise.
- Do not start or stop dev servers unless the brief says to.
- End with the structured final report the brief asks for (files touched, commands run
  with real exit status, open questions). Your diff will be independently reviewed —
  report honestly, including failures.
